Unknown people have killed a member of the Ebubeagu security network in Ebonyi State. It was gathered that the victim, 32-year-old Ifeanyi Orogbowhow, was murdered and partially burnt by the attackers. The incident, it was further gathered, occurred in the night in Igweledeoha, Amagu in Ikwo Local Government Area. The attack and murder took place at a drinking joint in the community which was said to be owned by the victim.   We’ll make Plateau hot for kidnappers, ritualists, others,…     Father, daughter arrested with fresh human parts in Osun     Gunmen kill one; abduct five along Lagos-Ibadan Expressway   Police spokesperson, Loveth Odah confirmed the incident. - Advertisement - She said: “The Divisional Police Officer (DPO) of Ikwo Police Division said “at about 3:00 a.m. that he received a phone call from one source at Igweledeoha Amagu Ikwo that one Ebubeagu security outfit, Ifeanyi Orogbo, 32-year-old who is indigenous to Igweledeoha was murdered and partially burnt by unknown people in his beer parlour shop along Eke Achara-Agubia Road. “The DPO said as he received the information, he quickly mobilised a team of police operatives to the area but the culprits had deserted the area. He said the corpse has been taken to a general hospital for preservation and autopsy.” The spokesperson said two persons suspected to be involved in the murder of the Ebubeagu official have been arrested by the police. She said the state Commissioner of Police, Garba Aliyu has expressed dismay over the killing of the Ebubeagu security official and has vowed to bring the perpetrators to book.